    narr:generatedFrom "c354f003fe2a54a8d5d3268a64e6f8923cccb163" ;
    narr:narration """The sequencing logic runs from mid-2025 through mid-2026. The earliest layer establishes [friendlies-before-paid discipline](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_FriendliesBeforePaidSequence) and a [phase gate model](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_FocusSequencing) (Phase 0 gift → F&F raise → first engagement → angel/seed from traction). By March 2026, scope triage sharpens: [only three tasks block V1](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ThreeBlockersOnly), [marketplace and starter perspectives fall below the line](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_BelowTheLine_April1), and [April 1 is set as the forcing function](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_April1ForcingFunction) for the paid-tier push. The [week of March 15 is explicitly scoped to testing and documentation](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_WeekPlanTestingConsolidation), not development. The [human-driven development principle](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_HumanDrivenDevelopmentPrinciple) — articulated March 31 — frames why unconstrained AI-assisted building is the structural risk the sequencing guards against. April surfaces [enterprise-shape as tentative primary sales focus](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus), with [enterprise consulting retained as revenue but removed from fundraising framing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseRemainsRevenue). June consolidates: [solo-partner v2 demo, codebase, content engine, YC draft, and the enterprise customer analytics](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_JuneConsolidationPlan) before the July fundraising push. July allocates [remaining Fable-class compute to the multi-pass extraction spike](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_FableWindowAllocationJul5) and sequences [angel-first, family as follow-on](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AngelFirstFamilyFollowOn). The [consulting discovery GTM wedge](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_DiscoveryToolGTMWedge) and [side-door entry pattern](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Insight_SideDoorGTM) offer alternative entry framings running alongside the product-led sequence.""" ;
